[{"text": "<!-- Page 1 -->", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "Resolutions adopted on the reports of the Fifth Committee 101", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "2990 (XXVII). United Nations International School", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "The General Assembly,", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "Having considered the report of the Secretary-General,32", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "Recognizing the important role of the United Nations International School in providing international education facilities of a high academic and cultural standard for children of the United Nations community in New York and the need to preserve the international character of the School,", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "Noting that this international character is being endangered by the diminishing percentage of the enrolment of children of United Nations staff members,", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "1. Decides, subject to review by the General Assembly at its twenty-ninth session, to increase the maximum of the education grant provided in regulation 3.2 of the Staff Regulations of the United Nations from $1,000 to $1,500, effective 1 January 1973, and to amend that regulation accordingly;", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "2. Urges, as increased funds become available in future years through the operation of the United Nations International School Development Fund, that consideration should be given to increasing bursaries, to the extent practicable, and using them as a means of attracting additional children from members of the diplomatic and consular corps who do not receive a substantial education grant from their Governments;", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "3. Appeals to Governments to continue to assist the United Nations International School to the extent possible, especially by providing scholarships and making available qualified teachers.", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "2111th plenary meeting", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "15 December 1972", "type": "frontmatter", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "3006 (XXVII). United Nations Juridical Yearbook33", "type": "title", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": null, "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "The General Assembly,", "type": "paragraph", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": "preambular", "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": null, "action_verb_type": null, "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "Recalling that, by its resolution 1814 (XVII) of 18 December 1962, it decided that the United Nations Juridical Yearbook should contain the documentary materials listed in the annex to that resolution,", "type": "paragraph", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": "preambular", "paragraph_level": null, "prefix": null, "action_verb": "Recalling", "action_verb_type": "preambular", "action_verb_normalized": null, "links": []}, {"text": "Having considered, at its twenty-sixth session, the comments concerning the United Nations Juridical Yearbook set forth in the report of the Joint Inspection Unit on the programme of recurrent publications of the United Nations34 and, at its twenty-seventh session, the views concerning the Yearbook contained in the report of the Secretary-General on the programme of recurrent publications,35", "type": "paragraph", "language": "english", "heading_level": null, "paragraph_type": "preambular", "paragraph_level": null, 